<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Gobi Rice Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/gopirice.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Gobi Rice Recipe</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="recipe-container">
       

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2 cups Cooked Basmati Rice</li>
                <li>1 cup Cauliflower (Gobi) florets</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
                <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
                <li>1 Onion (finely chopped)</li>
                <li>1 Tomato (finely chopped)</li>
                <li>1 tsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
                <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
                <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
                <li>1 tsp Garam Masala</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Fresh Coriander for garnish</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Boil cauliflower florets in hot water with salt for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li>
                <li>Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds, and let them splutter.</li>
                <li>Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
                <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook for a minute.</li>
                <li>Add tomatoes, chili powder, turmeric, and garam masala. Cook until oil separates.</li>
                <li>Add boiled cauliflower florets and mix well.</li>
                <li>Add cooked rice and salt. Stir gently until well combined.</li>
                <li>Garnish with fresh coriander and serve hot.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
